======================================================================
FINAL SUMMARY
======================================================================

DETECTION CORRECTION EFFECT ON WELLS INTERACTION ESTIMATE
==========================================================
  Standard model:         β = -1.394 [-1.941, -0.870]  P(<0)=1.000
  Detection-corrected:    β = -1.836 [-2.737, -1.067]  P(<0)=1.000
  Change in β:            -0.442
  Interpretation: Detection correction amplifies the Wells effect estimate

HIDDEN STRAY ANALYSIS (53 Undetected Group B Fish)
====================================================
  Expected true Entiat returners (missed at ENL): 20.1  (39%)
  Expected hidden Methow strays:                  1.1  (2%)
  Expected hidden Okanogan strays:                0.1  (0%)
  Other/died:                                     29.7  (58%)

  Total expected hidden strays: 1.2 fish (2% of undetected)
  These hidden strays, if confirmed, would reduce the apparent
  Wells interaction effect (Group B true Entiat return rate goes UP;
  true stray rate goes UP too, partially offsetting each other).

DETECTION-CORRECTED RETURN RATES
==================================
  Group A: 89.7% → 93.4% (raw → corrected)
  Group B: 68.0% → 79.1% (raw → corrected)
  Both groups' true return rates are higher than raw observed rates,
  but the RELATIVE difference between groups is what drives the
  Wells interaction coefficient.

